3c12c51e88676a5cfb294ed45/icons/128x128/org.kde.akregator.pngkdescriptionsKDE RSS feed readerpdescription_longyAkregator is a news feed reader. It enables you to follow news sites, blogs and other RSS/Atom-enabled websites without the need to manually check for updates using a web browser. Akregator is designed to be both easy to use and to be powerful enough to read hundreds of news sources conveniently. It comes with a fast search, advanced archiving functionality and an internal browser for easy news reading. kscreenshotsxlhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/kde/akregator/4e4a4193c12c51e88676a5cfb294ed45/screenshots/image-1_orig.pnggversiong25.04.0ldownload_urlx_oci://ghcr.io/pkgforge/pkgcache/akregator/runimage/alpine/stable/akregator:25.04.0-x86_64-linuxdsizef324 MBjbuild_datet2025-04-25T18:58:59Zhsrc_urlsx$https://invent.kde.org/pim/akregatorhweb_urlsxhttps://apps.kde.org/akregatorlbuild_scriptx]https://github.com/pkgforge/soarpkgs/blob/main/packages/akregator/runimage.alpine.stable.yamlibuild_logxhttps://api.ghcr.pkgforge.dev/pkgforge/pkgcache/akregator/runimage/alpine/stable/akregator?tag=25.04.0-x86_64-linux&download=akregator.logjcategoriesqNetwork,News,FeedisnapshotsÂfcommitt24.12.0-x86_64-linuxgversiong24.12.0Âfcommitt24.12.1-x86_64-linuxgversiong24.12.1Âfcommitt24.12.2-x86_64-linuxgversiong24.12.2Âfcommitt24.12.3-x86_64-linuxgversiong24.12.3glicenselBSD-3-Clausekmaintainersx*Azathothas (https://github.com/Azathothas)enotesxRBuilt Using RunImage [alpine]. Check/Report @ https://github.com/VHSgunzo/runimagex@Learn more @ https://docs.pkgforge.dev/formats/packages/runimagex[PORTABLE] (Works on AnyLinux)drankîÑcpkgxelement-desktop.runimagehpkg_nameoelement-desktopfpkg_idxrunimage.alpine.element-desktopfapp_idlim.riot.Riotdiconxihttps://dl.flathub.org/media/im/riot/Riot/8ec9953759013c3d6b9173c6b2ba8977/icons/128x128/im.riot.Riot.pngkdescriptionx0A glossy Matrix collaboration client for desktoppdescription_longyÅMore than group chat: communication

 
Communicate with your team and out of network colleagues more efficiently: use dedicated rooms which persist information from their creation and forever. 
Forget group emails: join or create rooms per topic, per team, per eventãÎ Decide the level of transparency you want to provide across the organisation or project. 
Cut through the noise by creating notifications that are customised by you and for you. 
Grab the attention of your colleague by calling out their name and donãt miss a thing with keyword alerts. 
Deploy bots for fun or practical use with our integrations store. 
 

Preliminary Wayland support since 1.7.25.

 To try running Element natively under Wayland, run:

 flatpak run im.riot.Riot --enable-features=UseOzonePlatform,WebRTCPipeWireCapturer --ozone-platform=wayland

